trators     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: British individuals, Females, Shop owners, Wizards         English     Polski   Русский               Primpernelle              View source                         History                         Talk (4)                                   Primpernelle   Biographical information  Born Before 1981[1]   Title(s) Madam[2]    Physical information  Species Human[2]   Gender Female[2]    Affiliation  Occupation Shop owner[2]   Loyalty Madam Primpernelle's Beautifying Potions[2]   [Source]  Madam Primpernelle was a witch who owned a shop called Madam Primpernelle's Beautifying Potions. It was located at 275 Diagon Alley and appeared in the Daily Prophet.[2]  Appearances Daily Prophet Newsletters (First mentioned) Notes and references   ↑ As she owned a business by 1999, she must have been 17 or older.  ↑ 2.0 2.1 2.2 2.3 2.4 2.5 Daily Prophet Newsletters: 8 February, 1999, Page 2    London's wizarding quarter   England, Great Britain   Carkitt Market - Diagon Alley - Horizont Alley - Knockturn Alley    Diagon Alley   Shops    2nd Hand Brooms ·  Amanuensis Quills ·  Broomstix ·  Broom Brakes Service ·  Broom Shop ·  Cauldron Workshop ·  Cranville Quincey's Magical Junkshop ·  Fine Enchanting Cauldrons ·  Floo-Pow ·  Florist's stall ·  Gambol and Japes Wizarding Joke Shop ·  J. Pippin's Potions ·  Jimmy Kiddell's Wonderful Wands ·  The Junk Shop ·  Madam Primpernelle's Beautifying Potions ·  Mr Mulpepper's Apothecary ·  Obscurus Books ·  Ollivanders ·  Rosa Lee Teabag ·  Scribbulus Writing Implements ·  Second-Hand Bookshop ·  Second-Hand Robes ·  Slug & Jiggers Apothecary ·  Sugarplum's Sweets Shop ·  Surgical and Dental Operator ·  Twilfitt and Tattings ·  Wand Showroom ·  Weasleys' Wizard Wheezes ·  Whizz Hard Books    Other services    Brews and Stews ·  Daily Prophet's main office ·  Diagon Alley stalls ·  GalloLoans ·  Gringotts Wizarding Bank ·  The Ministry Press ·  Peter Boat ·  TerrorTours  